In regards to the protests of the vietnam war, it was the backlash of the silent majority that brought the war to a close.  It was not those radicals that burned draft cards or<br>
called soldiers &quot;baby killers&quot;, that ended the war.  The true fustration of military involvement was voiced by the parents, friends and relatives of men who went off to fight the war.  When the middle class of America saw its sons come home killed and wounded for a war with no goals or measurable progress it demanded the end.  Our government couldn't ignore this cry, like it could with the radicals in our colleges.  This is the protes that ended the war.   
